column5: Anyone know if le baron still  has reasonable stock of terminal tackle and lures?
Lure selection isn't too bad considering the sale has been going on for a few weeks, everything else is getting scarce, somehow I still managed to spend 300$ today

I just did a fall clean up of all my tackle in my Man closet, Man sheds and my boat. I have a few thousand dollars of tackle I haven't used in 15 years. Unfortunately somehow water got into a few trays in my built in trays on the StarCraft, 8 in total and I threw our a few hundred bucks worth or more, I cried like a baby. Take it from me be careful or you too will become a tackle hoarder. I stopped at a local Swap shop TODAY in Cayuga and bought more reels I don't need and will probably never use. Happy shopping, can I join you?

No clue about the Markam store, I went to the Mississauga store today, it's been well picked over, that's for sure, I still walked out for $203 with this stuff, that reel is $235 retail alone plus tax
Chris let me make an offer on the Currado 200.

If it was a week ago maybe, not now.....I went on Friday the 4th, they had lots of lures, reels, and rods. I went back on the 7th and basically it was all gone. So that was a week ago, Id imagine most things are cleared out.
